Configuring API server --> https://github.com/typicode/json-server

Getting started --> Install JSON Server

1 - Go to your terminal and do ---> npm install -g json-server

2 - create a text file, name the text file --> db.json

3 - copy and paste the below in the the json file and save it

{
  "posts": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "automation",
      "author": "John"
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "title": "dummyTitle",
      "auther": "Max"
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "title": "automation",
      "author": "John"
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "title": "Science",
      "author": "Mike"
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "title": "Engineering",
      "author": "Philips"
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "title": "Science",
      "author": "Mike"
    }
  ]
}

4 - Go to the root folder where you save db.json and start the server -->  json-server --watch db.json

5 - Your application should now be up and running - -> http://localhost:3000/posts

To run all the test
* mvn test -Dtest=TestRunner

